      consultantWording: 'This [age]-year-old [gender] with [vascular risk factors] presented with [symptom] [duration] after LKW. NIHSS was [score] on arrival. NCCT brain showed [ASPECTS score, findings] with no haemorrhage. CTA revealed [LVO/stenosis/dissection/normal]. [Thrombolysis with alteplase/TNK was given at [time] post-LKW / No thrombolysis due to [reason].] [Thrombectomy was performed at [time] achieving TICI [grade] recanalisation / No thrombectomy due to [reason].] Diagnosis: Acute ischaemic stroke in [territory] due to [TOAST aetiology]. Plan: Admit to [ward/HDU/ICU]. [Aspirin/anticoagulation]. Atorvastatin [dose]. BP goal [target]. Dysphagia status: [safe/NG tube pending]. Rehabilitation: [PT/OT/SLT referrals].',
      exampleNote: 'A 62-year-old male with hypertension and type 2 diabetes presented at 14:30 with LKW at 12:00 (onset 2.5h ago). FAST positive: left facial droop, left arm drift, slurred speech. NIHSS 12 (1a:1, 1b:1, 1c:1, 6:2, 7:2, 8:2, 9:2, 10:1). BP 165/95, BGL 8.2 mmol/L. NCCT brain: ASPECTS 9 (loss of insular ribbon). CTA: right MCA-M1 occlusion. Patient within 4.5h window, no contraindications to tPA. Alteplase 0.9 mg/kg (total 72 mg: 7.2 mg bolus, 64.8 mg infusion) started at 15:00 (door-to-needle 40 min). Transferred for thrombectomy: right MCA-M1 stent retriever, TICI 2b recanalisation at 17:00. Door-to-puncture: 2h. Post-procedure CT: no haemorrhage. Admitted to HDU for 24h monitoring. BP controlled. Diagnosis: Acute right MCA ischaemic stroke (LAA: right MCA-M1 occlusion). Plan: Aspirin 300 mg after 24h CT (confirm no haemorrhage). Atorvastatin 80 mg nocte. BP target <140/90 acute then <130/80. Dysphagia: failed water swallow test, keep NBM, SLT review. PT/OT daily. Review for long-term anticoagulation (prolonged Holter for paroxysmal AF).',
